##### <span id="index"></span>IBIS Queue

The IBIS queue is a intermediate storage area used for RESTful data
processing. Unlike the staging area where it deals with connector data,
the IBIS queue can be used to temporarily store other types of data
(like notification messages)

To view the IBIS queue: click on the "All pages" menu item. When the
sidepanel opens click on "IBIS queue" menu item.

The IBIS queue can:

-   Receive messages that will be placed in the queue waiting to be send
-   Process messages after which the status will be modified
